{"id": "EUVD-2022-55255", "enisaUuid": "58f64318-f3fd-3c30-9836-7597139c544a", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nbpf: Don't redirect packets with invalid pkt_len\n\nSyzbot found an issue [1]: fq_codel_drop() try to drop a flow whitout any\nskbs, that is, the flow->head is null.\nThe root cause, as the [2] says, is because that bpf_prog_test_run_skb()\nrun a bpf prog which redirects empty skbs.\nSo we should determine whether the length of the packet modified by bpf\nprog or others like bpf_prog_test is valid before forwarding it directly.", "datePublished": "2025-06-18T11:00:38", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-23T13:26:14", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8b68e53d56697a59b5c53893b53f508bbdf272a0", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6204bf78b2a903b96ba43afff6abc0b04d6e0462", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a75987714bd2d8e59840667a28e15c1fa5c47554", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/72f2dc8993f10262092745a88cb2dd0fef094f23", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/fd1894224407c484f652ad456e1ce423e89bb3eb", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-49975"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49975"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0b468acc-1448-3990-833d-773a8a9c09ac", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.65"}, {"id": "340e9dcf-0e3f-3299-98b1-a2b2f44fdb7f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.10.141"}, {"id": "3831bf4f-07a7-3878-bedc-8dd0979095dc", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <8b68e53d56697a59b5c53893b53f508bbdf272a0"}, {"id": "3fc3b5df-d51a-397a-9280-d4964bb61c3e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.0"}, {"id": "46362a2c-4a7b-3a2a-94bd-c1e5fb3063de", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <a75987714bd2d8e59840667a28e15c1fa5c47554"}, {"id": "497daf6a-fdac-3947-912c-60fd591e312b", "product": {"name